Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Permission denied reading system files

Solution: Use sudo for system configuration files or run scripts with elevated privileges
Issue: Network monitoring shows no connections

Solution: Ensure network activity is occurring; try sudo apt update in another terminal
Issue: TLS connection timeouts

Solution: Check firewall settings; verify internet connectivity; some servers may block automated connections
Issue: Python module import errors

Solution: Install required modules: pip3 install --user <module_name>
Conclusion
This lab provided hands-on experience analyzing software update mechanisms for supply chain security risks. Students learned to identify vulnerabilities in package managers, monitor network traffic, evaluate TLS security, and create automated auditing tools. These skills are essential for securing software supply chains and preventing compromise through update mechanisms.

